Lindsey Anne Olson and John Peter Collins Jr. were married March 24 in New Orleans. J. Peter Collins, a retired Kent Town justice and the groom’s father, officiated at the Degas House, the former home of the family of the artist Edgar Degas.
The couple, who are both 32 and litigation associates at law firms in New York, met at Fordham, from which each received a law degree cum laude.
The bride, who is taking her husband’s name, works at Proskauer Rose. She graduated cum laude from Princeton.
She is a daughter of Dr. Laurie H. Olson and Steven G. Olson of New Orleans. Her mother is a child psychologist in private practice there; she specializes in treatment of children with autism. The bride’s father owns an architecture firm, which bears his name, in New Orleans.
The groom, who goes by JP, works at Sullivan & Cromwell. He graduated from Stonehill College in Easton, Mass.
He is a son of Martha G. Collins and Judge Collins of Kent Lakes, N.Y. The groom’s mother is the executive director of the Putnam Community Foundation, a nonprofit organization in Brewster, N.Y., that aims to improve the quality of life of older Putnam County residents. His father is now of counsel at Feldman, Kleidman, Coffey, Sappe & Regenbaum, a law firm in Fishkill, N.Y.
